The Situation Room
Live from Washington
Wednesday, April 25, 2007

IN POLITICS:
•	House Majority Leader: “Solution in Iraq is a Political Solution”
•	House Committee Votes to Subpoena Rice over Africa Uranium Claim
•	Rep. Hunter Calls for Reid to Step Down Over “War is Lost” Remarks

IN THE NEWS:
•	Tornado Slams Texas-Mexico Border Community; 10 Dead
•	Dow Hits New Mark

IN THE CAFFERTY FILE:
•	Will 9/11 politics help or hurt Rudy Giuliani in the presidential race?
•	Who gets too much, or too little, attention from Washington lawmakers?
•	Should Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice be forced to testify about pre-war intelligence on Iraq?

